<subSubSection id="64EA50C123333180C192F166F910124E" pageId="21" pageNumber="32" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="5775F46F27E00C71E7FF56A8F8FE9DC2" pageId="21" pageNumber="32">Etymology.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="1091C10D81A293886BFC499C1A8F25D2" pageId="21" pageNumber="32">
The name of this genus is from the Greek, meaning 
<normalizedToken id="7506EC17BBA20A2B16C676873314607A" originalValue="‘pill-shaped’">'pill-shaped'</normalizedToken>
; feminine.
</paragraph>
